\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line Damelin \'28Pty\'29 Ltd is registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training as a private higher education institution and has programmes accredited by the CHE.\line \line The Institution applied for accreditation of the Higher Certificate in Project Management which was tabled at the HEQC meeting held on the 13th of February 2020.\line \line The programme was not accredited for the following reasons\'3A\line 1. The Institution has not provided an explanation as to how the programme purpose will be achieved as only 15 credits are dedicated to Project Management which is the qualifier in the programme.\line 2. While there is a WIL component of 15 credits there is very little detail provided on the management of WIL and the integration of this component in the curriculum of the programme focused on Project Management. \line 3. The Institution has not explained how students with low numeracy or with no background in Finance will be able to manage this programme given the Accounting and Statistics modules in the programme. \line 4. The statement in the submission that both formative and summative assessment is conducted by the respective institutions as outlined in the Assessment Policy has not been clarified as well as the management of assessments at the different sites of delivery. \line 5. The Institution has not provided an explanation of how it intends to implement assessment and teaching and learning ensuring equivalence of provisioning across all campuses as the programme is proposed for offering on multiple campuses.\line 6. The Institution has not clarified the four \'284\'29 different types of assessments mentioned and whether formative assessment marks count towards the summative total\'3B including the number of assessments to be completed to calculate the semester marks\'2C year marks and final marks.\line \line The Institution submitted a representation which has been evaluated.\cell \pard 

\intbl \row \pard 
\line \par\pard\trowd\trqc \trpaddl113\trpaddt113\trpaddb113\trpaddr113\trpaddfl3\trpaddft3\trpaddfb3\trpaddfr3\trgaph100\trrh100\trleft36
